text: This is a list of exoplanets. *51 Pegasi b, a gas giant 51 light years away in the constellation Pegasus. *47 Ursae Majoris b, a gas giant 46 light years away in the constellation Ursa Major. *55 Cancri e, a rocky planet 41 light years away in the constellation Cancer. *70 Virginis b, a rocky planet 60 light years away in the constellation Virgo. *COROT-7b, a rocky planet 490 light years away in the constellation Monoceros. *Gliese 581 c, a rocky planet 20 light years away in the constellation Libra (was once believed to be habitable). *Gliese 667 Cc, a rocky planet 23.6 light years away in the constellation Scorpius (may be habitable). *GQ Lupi b, a gas giant located 502 light yeaes away in the constellation Lupus *HD 85512b, a rocky planet 36 light years away in the constellation Vela *HD 100546b(en), a gas giant 316 light years away in the constellation Musca *HD 189733b, a hot Jupiter gas giant located 63 light years away in the constellation Vulpeca. *Kepler-22b, a super-earth 640 light years away in the constellation Cygnus. (may be habitable) *Kepler-62d, a rocky planet 1,200 light years away in the constellation Lyra. *Kepler-62e, a rocky planet 1,200 light years away in the constellation Lyra (may be habitable). *Kepler-62f, a rocky planet 1,200 light years away in the constellation Lyra (may be habitable). *Kepler-186f, a rocky planet 580+ light years away in the constellation Cygnus (may be habitable). *Kepler-441b, an ice planet over 1,200 light planet away. *Kepler-442b, a rocky planet over 1,000 light years away in the constellation Lyra (may be habitable). *Kepler-452b, a rocky planet over 1,400 light years away in the constellation Cygnus (may be habitable). *PSR B1257+12 B, a rocky planet going around a pulsar 980 light years away in the constellation Virgo. *Qatar-5b *TrES-2b, a gas giant 704 light years away in the constellation Draco (Darkest planet we know). *Proximal Centauri B - The first exoplanet found in the Proxima Centauri system. Could be habitable. *Proxima Centauri C *Proxima Centauri D *HAT P-7b. *Trappist 1 planets. *XO-3b *J1407b, an exoplanet with a ring system 200 times bigger than Saturn's *PSR B1620-26 b, a gas giant 12,400 light-years away in the constellation Scorpius * Category:Astronomy lists
title: List of exoplanets
